    <div class="right-col">
      <!-- Cleansing (Detoxification) -->
      <section class="card">
        <h2>Cleansing (Detoxification)</h2>
        <p>Cleansing supports your body’s elimination of metabolic waste and environmental toxins that can burden immune function.</p>
        <ul class="bullets">
          <li>May reduce inflammation burden and improve energy.</li>
          <li>Supports organs of elimination (liver, kidneys, gut, skin).</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="ref">
          <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6163475/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Research: Environmental chemicals &amp; chronic disease (review)</a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Antioxidants -->
      <section class="card">
        <h2>Antioxidants</h2>
        <p>Antioxidants protect cells from oxidative stress and lipid peroxidation — processes linked to immune dysfunction and chronic disease.</p>
        <ul class="bullets">
          <li>Dietary antioxidants help neutralize excess free radicals.</li>
          <li>Associated with reduced risk of cardiometabolic and neurodegenerative disease.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="ref">
          <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3249911/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Research: Oxidative stress, antioxidants &amp; disease (review)</a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Essential Nutrients -->
      <section class="card">
        <h2>Essential Nutrients</h2>
        <p>Immune cells require steady supplies of vitamins, minerals, amino acids, and healthy fats. Even mild deficiencies can impair defenses.</p>
        <ul class="bullets">
          <li>Targeted nutrient testing can reveal hidden gaps.</li>
          <li>Correcting deficiencies improves immune competence.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="ref">
          <a href="https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fimmu.2018.03160/full" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Frontiers: Immunity &amp; micronutrients (review)</a> ·
          <a href="https://ods.od.nih.gov/factsheets/VitaminD-Consumer/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">NIH ODS: Vitamin D</a> ·
          <a href="https://ods.od.nih.gov/factsheets/VitaminC-Consumer/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">NIH ODS: Vitamin C</a> ·
          <a href="https://ods.od.nih.gov/factsheets/Zinc-Consumer/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">NIH ODS: Zinc</a>
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>

  

  <style>
    /* Intro box */
    .intro-box {
      background-color: #f0f8ff;
      border-left: 5px solid #004080;
      padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
      margin-top: 2rem;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      border-radius: 10px;
      line-height: 1.6;
      box-shadow: 0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,.08);
    }

    /* NEW: Asymmetric two-column grid */
    .asym-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1.15fr 1fr; /* left slightly wider */
      gap: 20px;
      align-items: start;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }
    .left-col .card { height: 100%; }
    .right-col > .card + .card { margin-top: 20px; } /* stack spacing on right */

    /* Fallback to single column on narrow screens */
    @media (max-width: 900px) {
      .asym-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .right-col > .card + .card { margin-top: 16px; }
    }

    /* Card visuals */
    .card {
      background: #ffffff;
      border: 1px solid #e6eef7;
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
      box-shadow: 0 2px 10px rgba(0,0,0,.06);
    }
    .card h2 { margin: 0 0 .5rem 0; color: #003366; }
    .bullets { margin: .5rem 0 1rem 1.25rem; }
    .bullets li { margin: .25rem 0; }

    /* Highlight/info sections */
    .highlight-box {
      background: #f9fbff;
      border-left: 6px solid #004080;
      padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
      margin: 1.5rem 0;
      border-radius: 10px;
      box-shadow: 0 2px 10px rgba(0,0,0,.06);
    }
    .info-box {
      border-left: 6px solid #004080;
      background: #f0f8ff;
      padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
      margin: 1.0rem 0 0.5rem 0;
      border-radius: 10px;
      box-shadow: 0 2px 10px rgba(0,0,0,.06);
    }
    .provider-callout {
      background: #fff;
      border: 1px dashed #8fb3d9;
      border-radius: 10px;
      padding: .75rem 1rem;
      margin-top: .75rem;
      display: inline-block;
    }

    /* Centering for bottom blue boxes */
    .centered-section { text-align: center; }
    .center-bullets { list-style-position: inside; padding: 0; margin: 1em 0; }
    .center-bullets li { margin: 0.5em 0; }

    /* Research links inside Liver box (left-aligned by default) */
    .research-links { margin-top: .5rem; }
    .research-links ol { margin: .5rem 0 .25rem 1.25rem; }
    .research-links .supplemental { margin: .5rem 0 0 1.25rem; }

    /* Finder grid */
    .grid-2 {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0,1fr));
      gap: 20px;
      margin-top: .75rem;
      margin-bottom: .75rem;
      text-align: left;
    }
    @media (max-width: 900px) { .grid-2 { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
    .grid-2 h3 { margin: .25rem 0 .25rem 0; color: #003366; }
    .ref { font-size: .95rem; color: #333; }

    .examples .note-small { margin-top: .5rem; color: #555; }
    .prompt {
      background: #fff;
      border-left: 4px solid #4CAF50;
      padding: .5rem 1rem;
      margin: .5rem 0 0 0;
      display: inline-block;
      text-align: left;
    }

    .btn {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: .5rem .85rem;
      border-radius: 8px;
      border: 1px solid #004080;
      text-decoration: none;
      color: #004080;
      font-weight: 600;
    }
    .btn:hover { background: #004080; color: #fff; }

    .note {
      background: #fff;
      border: 1px solid #e6eef7;
      border-radius: 10px;
      padding: .75rem 1rem;
      margin-top: 1rem;
      display: inline-block;
      text-align: left;
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
